The Vikatgad fort once served as silos for storing grains under the rule of Shivaji Maharaj. Now, it holds adventure, scenic viewpoints and loads of fun for thrill seeking trekkers. One can also spot the famous hillstation--Matheran from here and a ridge that connects the two. Other famous peaks and forts such as Irshaal, Prabalgad and Malanggad can also be spotted. This fort is also known as Peb, with the name derived from Goddess Pebi.

Major Attractions
•	Experience the thrill of a monsoon Trek
•	Witness the beauty of the fort and the glory of nature
•	Enjoy a panoramic view of the Sahyadris.
•	Explore and learn its significance in history
